---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

// Constants
const title = "Services";
const description = "How I Can Help You Build & Grow";
---

<BaseLayout {title} {description}>
  <section 
    aria-label="terms of service" 
    class="mb-20 px-5 mt-20"
  >
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
        📜 Terms of Service
      </h1>

      <p class="mb-12 text-lg text-zinc-600">These terms apply when you use or download any of our Framer templates made by <span class="font-semibold">ScriptingPixels</span>. By using our stuff, you're agreeing to everything below.</p>

      <div class="space-y-10 text-base leading-7">
        
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold flex items-center gap-2">
            🧾 1. Overview
          </h2>
          <p>These Terms of Service govern your use of ScriptingPixels Framer templates and other digital assets. By purchasing, downloading, or using a template, you accept these terms in full.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold flex items-center gap-2">
            🔞 2. Eligibility
          </h2>
          <p>You must be at least 18 years old and legally allowed to enter contracts to use our templates.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold flex items-center gap-2">
            🧩 3. Products and Licensing
          </h2>
          <p>All templates are released under the <strong>GNU General Public License v3.0</strong> (GPL-3.0). You’re allowed to:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc ml-6 mt-2 space-y-1">
            <li>✅ Use, modify, and share templates, even commercially</li>
            <li>📢 Attribute the original source when redistributing</li>
            <li>🚫 Not restrict others when sharing modified versions</li>
            <li>🎨 Figma and non-code assets are excluded unless stated</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-zinc-500">Play fair. Don’t misrepresent, resell without modification, or pretend it’s 100% your original work.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold flex items-center gap-2">
            💳 4. Payment
          </h2>
          <p>All payments are processed securely via [your platform, e.g. Lemon Squeezy]. Prices are in USD and may not include taxes or additional fees.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold flex items-center gap-2">
            ❌ 5. Refunds
          </h2>
          <p>Digital products are non-refundable. All sales are final. If something breaks, reach out — we’ll do our best to help.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold flex items-center gap-2">
            🛠️ 6. Support & Updates
          </h2>
          <p>We offer email support and free updates when available. Support covers help with the template, not full-blown custom dev or Framer coaching.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold flex items-center gap-2">
            ⚖️ 7. Intellectual Property
          </h2>
          <p>Code is licensed under GPL-3.0. However, the ScriptingPixels brand, site content, and unique design elements remain ours unless explicitly released.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold flex items-center gap-2">
            💬 8. Feedback
          </h2>
          <p>If you leave a review or send feedback, we may use it to promote ScriptingPixels (your email stays private, though).</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold flex items-center gap-2">
            ⛔ 9. Termination
          </h2>
          <p>If you abuse the license, misrepresent the work, or breach this Agreement, we reserve the right to revoke access to updates or services.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold flex items-center gap-2">
            ⚙️ 10. Third-Party Services
          </h2>
          <p>We rely on tools like Framer and Lemon Squeezy. Using our templates means you also agree to their terms and policies.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold flex items-center gap-2">
            🌍 11. Governing Law
          </h2>
          <p>This agreement is governed by the laws of Uruguay. Disputes will be resolved through local courts, if it ever comes to that.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold flex items-center gap-2">
            🚨 12. Liability Disclaimer
          </h2>
          <p>ScriptingPixels isn't responsible for bugs, downtime, or losses caused by using the templates. Use them at your own risk.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold flex items-center gap-2">
            🔐 13. Privacy
          </h2>
          <p>Check out our <a href="/privacy-policy" class="underline text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-500">Privacy Policy</a> to see how we handle data.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-16 border-t pt-6 text-sm text-zinc-500">
        <p>Have questions? <a href="https://www.x.com/leandroubilla_" class="underline text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-500">Contact me on X</a>.</p>
        <p class="mt-2">Thanks for using ScriptingPixels.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
